ether with literature data of the mass-loss\nrates, our sample is consistent with a hypothesis that stars with low mass-loss\nrates form primarily dust that preserves the spectral properties of Al2O3, and\nstars with higher mass-loss rate form dust with properties of warm silicates.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 7 Oct 2013 20:00:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-17"}
